# Architecture Guardrails

This rule defines implementation patterns that are NOT allowed in this repository.

The agent must refuse or correct implementations that violate these guardrails.

---

# 1 Vendor Identity Rules

Vendor identity must only come from the JWT claim:

bcpAuth

Never derive vendor identity from:

request body
query parameters
headers
path variables

If vendor identity is missing from JWT, the request must be rejected.

---

# 2 Gateway Boundary Rules

The platform uses three logical gateways.

Admin Gateway
Purpose: governance and configuration
Endpoints:
  /v1/registry/**
  /v1/audit/**
  /v1/admin/**

Vendor Gateway
Purpose: vendor self-service
Endpoints:
  /v1/vendor/**

Runtime Gateway
Purpose: execution
Endpoints:
  /v1/execute
  /v1/ai/execute

Endpoints must never appear in the wrong gateway.

Example violations:

❌ exposing /v1/registry on vendor gateway
❌ exposing /v1/execute on admin gateway

---

# 3 Runtime Safety Rules

Execution flow must always follow:

1 authenticate
2 resolve vendor identity
3 enforce allowlist
4 validate contract
5 transform payload
6 call downstream endpoint
7 validate response
8 emit audit event
9 emit usage event

The runtime must never skip:

allowlist validation
contract validation
audit emission

---

# 4 PHI Protection Rules

PHI must never be stored in:

usage tables
billing tables
metrics tables

Examples of PHI:

memberId
member name
DOB
claim number
provider identifiers

PHI may only appear in:

data_plane transaction storage
audit payloads with redaction

Sensitive payload expansion requires:

PHI approved group
explicit reason
audit event

Secrets must always remain redacted.

---

# 5 Billing / Usage Rules

Usage events must only contain metadata.

Allowed fields:

vendor_code
operation_code
api_surface
status_code
latency
request_bytes
response_bytes
ai_tokens_in
ai_tokens_out
timestamp

Not allowed:

payloads
member identifiers
claim identifiers
response bodies

Usage emission must be fail-open.

Execution must never fail because usage recording failed.

---

# 6 Repository Structure Rules

The repository is a monorepo.

Backend code must live under:

apps/api

Admin UI must live under:

apps/web-cip

Vendor UI must live under:

apps/web-partners

Do not create directories named:

backend
frontend
client
server

---

# 7 Contract Authority

The canonical contract is defined in:

control_plane.operation_contracts

Vendor overrides may exist in:

control_plane.vendor_operation_contracts

Runtime validation must always use:

vendor override if present
otherwise canonical contract

---

# 8 Allowlist Authority

Allowed integrations are defined in:

control_plane.vendor_operation_allowlist

If no allowlist entry exists, execution must be denied.

Wildcard access must not be assumed.

---

# 9 AI Formatter Safety

AI formatter may enhance formatting but must never:

change business outcome
change routing decisions
skip validation

AI failures must not break execution.

---

# 10 Required Behavior When Guardrails Are Violated

If an implementation request violates any rule above, the agent must:

1 explain the violation
2 propose the correct architectural solution
3 refuse unsafe implementation